text: What type of personalities fit in best at your company?
The Great Gatsby - I think that's a great book because it manages to be readable and a classic without having a single likeable character in it. That's a sign of good writing!

In terms of personalities - probably inquisitive people are the best fit. We have an office full of intelligent people who like talk and writing about problems and interesting things, so wanting to learn more and understand more problems is probably the best asset
